"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1013178","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-12-03","<p>No assessment has been made. We engage across Government to ensure that health policy and delivery needs are taken into account in and also respond to wider policy developments.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-12-03T11:59:38.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1013178/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1013178/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1013178/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-11-23","Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what estimate he has made of the effect of changes in the level of welfare benefits on demand for NHS services.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","195132"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1013179","Church Commissioners","false","2018-11-27","<p>The underlying financial health of the Church of England’s parishes is a testament to the generosity of the commitment of congregations and local communities across the country. The most recent assessment of Church of England parish finances relate to 2016 when total giving to the 12,400 parishes was £3million more than the previous year. Between 2010 and 2016 total giving increased by 8.5%.</p><p /> <p>The figures also show that in 2016 Church of England parishes donated £46 million to supporting other charities working in the UK around the world, from foodbanks and local children's charities to international aid appeals.</p><p /> <p>Detailed figures for giving and charitable donations can be found in the 2016 Parish Finances Statistics here: <a href="https://www.churchofengland.org/sites/default/files/2018-10/2016ParishFinanceStatistics.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.churchofengland.org/sites/default/files/2018-10/2016ParishFinanceStatistics.pdf</a></p>","Meriden","Dame Caroline Spelman",,"2018-11-27T17:17:27.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1013179/answer","Biography information for Dame Caroline Spelman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1013179/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1013179/answer",,,,,,,,"9","Church Commissioners","Church Commissioners","2018-11-23","Charitable Donations","1","House of Commons","To ask the right hon. Member for Meriden, representing the Church Commissioners, what assessment the Church Commissioners have made of trends in the level of demand for charitable donations since 2010.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","195133"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1013180","Church Commissioners","false","2018-11-27","<p>The Church Commissioners receive no direct Government support for maintaining redundant or under-utilised churches.</p><p> </p><p>The Church Commissioners and DCMS provide financial support for the Churches Conservation Trust, which cares for redundant churches of special architectural significance, and for which no suitable alternative use can be found. The Grants to the Churches Conservation Trust Order 2016, (which can be found here: <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukdsi/2016/9780111142738" target="_blank">https://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukdsi/2016/9780111142738</a>) sets out the basis of Government funding from 1<sup>st</sup> April 2016 to 31<sup>st</sup> March 2020.</p>","Meriden","Dame Caroline Spelman",,"2018-11-27T17:19:29.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1013180/answer","Biography information for Dame Caroline Spelman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1013180/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1013180/answer",,,,,,,,"9","Church Commissioners","Church Commissioners","2018-11-23","Churches: Repairs and Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the right hon. Member for Meriden, representing the Church Commissioners, what support the Church Commissioners receive from Her Majesty's Government to enable them to maintain (a) redundant and (b) under-utilised churches.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","195134"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1013181","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-12-03","<p>The modelling prepared by Public Health England which supported the Joint Committee on Vaccination and Immunisation recommendation to move to a 1+1 schedule for Pneumococcal Conjugate Vaccine has been submitted for publication in a peer reviewed journal, and will be published in due course.</p><p> </p><p>There are no plans to share the paper with stakeholders ahead of publication.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-12-03T17:09:32.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1013181/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1013181/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1013181/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-11-23","Pneumococcal Diseases: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, pursuant to the Answer of 24 October to Question 180205 on Pneumococcal Diseases: Vaccination, whether his Department will make the modelling paper available to stakeholders ahead of (a) any decision on a change to the pneumococcal vaccination schedule and (b) ahead of its publication in a peer reviewed journal.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","195079"
