"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012342","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-11-27","<p>We have made no assessment of the impact on patient safety of such a service. Where clinical commissioning groups have made local arrangements for how repeat medication is ordered we would expect it to take account of the General Medical Council’s Prescribing Guidance, so repeat prescriptions are safe and appropriate to patient need.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-11-27T17:13:09.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012342/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012342/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012342/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-11-22","Prescriptions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment he has made of the effect on patient safety of the roll out by clinical commissioning groups of the prescription ordering direct service for repeat prescriptions.","false","Biography information for Rosie Cooper","West Lancashire","Rosie Cooper","194650"
